An overturned private car at the junction of Muindi Mbingu and Kenyatta Avenue on Tuesday, February 8, 2022, after it was involved in an accident with a Nissan matatu. [Collins Kweyu, Standard]  Three women sustained serious injuries yesterday morning when a private car they were travelling in was involved in accident with a matatu at the junction of Kenyatta Avenue and Muindi Mbingu Street in Nairobi.  A traffic police officer at the scene blamed the accident on the matatu driver he accused of refusing to give way to the private car that had the right of way.  The car overturned on impact after it was hit by the matatu that was said to have been speeding.         By Josphat Thiongó | 5 hours ago By Collins Kweyu | 15 hours ago By Kamau Muthoni | 15 hours ago By Collins Kweyu | 1 day ago